a-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 03, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104nuj1690355978702.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nuj1690355978702.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nuj1690355978702.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"vbe1665702794855\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                           \n Define Frames Worksheet \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Use the Define Frames worksheet to graphically create both the component data\n    structure and layout of Form and Report components. </p>\n<div class=\"p\" id=\"vbe1665702794855__p_d5489e1_d5490e1_d5491e1\">To do so, select an object in the Resource Browser and draw\n      it as a frame on the Canvas pane (the central area of the editor). Additionally, you can also\n      insert or paste fields in the Structure pane, but not in the Canvas pane.<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"vbe1665702794855__note_rqg_bsb_gyb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> You can insert or paste multiple fields in one attempt in the\n        Structure pane.</div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vbe1665702794855__p_d5492e1_d5493e1_d5494e1\">Frames are used to represent data objects (such as entities, fields, and labels), layout objects (such as lines and area frames), and print objects (such as header, footer, and break frames).</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vbe1665702794855__section_rxg_x32_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d594279e63\">Tools</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"vbe1665702794855__ul_hmg_y32_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vbe1665702794855__li_d2600e1_d2601e1_d2602e1\">Canvas—represents the runtime component, and provides a\n          canvas on which to draw and arrange entities, occurrences, fields and graphical elements\n          of the component layout. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vbe1665702794855__li_d2603e1_d2604e1_d2605e1\">Resource Browser—choose modeled entities, objects, or\n          templates to insert on the Canvas. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vbe1665702794855__li_d2606e1_d2607e1_d2608e1\">Structure—shows the component structure as a tree. It\n          enables you to select and delete objects, but to add objects, you must draw them using the\n          Canvas. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vbe1665702794855__li_d2609e1_d2610e1_d2611e1\">Properties Inspector—shows the properties of the object\n          selected in the Structure or Canvas, and enables you to edit them. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vbe1665702794855__section_vkn_y32_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d594279e84\">How to </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"vbe1665702794855__ul_gtm_z32_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vbe1665702794855__li_d2612e1_d2613e1_d2614e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cvl1690356504825.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cvl1690356504825.html\" title=\"Use the Define Frames worksheet to graphically define both the component data structure and the layout of the component.\">Define the Structure and Layout of Forms and Reports</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vbe1665702794855__li_d2615e1_d2616e1_d2617e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lfh1665702612528.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lfh1665702612528.html\" title=\"Use the Define Frames worksheet to refine the layout of the form component.\">Design the Layout of Forms</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vbe1665702794855__li_d2618e1_d2619e1_d2620e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"erz1665702688168.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/erz1665702688168.html\" title=\"Use the Define Frames worksheet to refine the layout of the Report component. You can add header and footer frames to define pages headers and footers, and break frames to control page break behavior.\">Design the Layout of Reports</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4443798\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4443798\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define Frames Worksheet Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 03, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define Frames Worksheet Use the Define Frames worksheet to graphically create both the component data structure and layout of Form and Report components. To do so, select an object in the Resource Browser and draw it as a frame on the Canvas pane (the central area of the editor). Additionally, you can also insert or paste fields in the Structure pane, but not in the Canvas pane. Note: You can insert or paste multiple fields in one attempt in the Structure pane. Frames are used to represent data objects (such as entities, fields, and labels), layout objects (such as lines and area frames), and print objects (such as header, footer, and break frames). Tools Canvas—represents the runtime component, and provides a canvas on which to draw and arrange entities, occurrences, fields and graphical elements of the component layout. Resource Browser—choose modeled entities, objects, or templates to insert on the Canvas. Structure—shows the component structure as a tree. It enables you to select and delete objects, but to add objects, you must draw them using the Canvas. Properties Inspector—shows the properties of the object selected in the Structure or Canvas, and enables you to edit them. How to Define the Structure and Layout of Forms and Reports Design the Layout of Forms Design the Layout of Reports Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}